atre]], [[Southampton]], England\n|-\n| Jun 7, 2007 - Jul 7, 2007 || ''[[Babes in Arms]]'' || Mrs. Phyllis Owen || [[Chichester Festival Theatre]], [[Chichester]], [[Sussex]], England\n|-\n| Nov 19, 2007 - Dec 8, 2007 || ''[[White Christmas (musical)|White Christmas]]'' || Martha Watson || [[Edinburgh Playhouse]], [[Edinburgh]], [[Scotland]]\n|-\n| Dec 13, 2007 - Jan 12, 2008 || ''[[White Christmas (musical)|White Christmas]]'' || Martha Watson || [[Wales Millennium Centre]], [[Cardiff]], [[Wales]]\n|-\n| Nov 29, 2008 - Jan 4, 2009 || ''[[The Wizard of Oz (1939 film)|The Wizard of Oz]]'' || [[Wicked Witch of the West]] || [[The Lowry]], [[Manchester]], England\n|-\n| Feb 2, 2009 - Apr 11, 2009 || ''[[Pack of Lies]]'' || Helen Kroger || UK National Tour\n|-\n| Nov 3, 2009 - Jan 10, 2010 || ''[[White Christmas (musical)|White Christmas]]'' || Martha Watson || US National Tour\n|-\n| Nov 16, 2011 - Dec 24, 2011 || ''[[White Christmas (musical)|White Christmas]]'' || Martha Watson || [[Paper Mill Playhouse]], [[Millburn, New Jersey]]\n|-\n| Apr 28, 2015 || ''[[Follies]]'' || Hattie Walker || [[Royal Albert Hall]], London, England\n|-\n| Nov 12, 2016 - Jan 1, 2017 || ''[[White Christmas (musical)|White Christmas]]'' || Martha Watson || US National Tour\n|-\n| Nov 24, 2017 - Dec 31, 2017 || ''[[Holiday Inn (musical)|Holiday Inn]]'' || Louise Badger || [[5th Avenue Theatre]], [[Seattle|Seattle, Washington]]\n|-\n| Nov 9, 2019 - Dec 29, 2019 || ''[[White Christmas (musical)|White Christmas]]'' || Martha Watson || US National Tour\n|-\n|}\n\n==Published works==\n* {{Cite book |last=Luft |first=Lorna |year= 1998 |title= Me and My Shadows: A Family Memoir |publisher= Simon & Schuster |isbn=978-0671019006}}\n* {{Cite book |last=Luft |first=Lorna |year= 2018 |title= A Star Is Born: Judy Garland and the Film That Got Away |publisher= Running Press |isbn=978-0762464807}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Lorna Luft}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20051026183701/http://www.lornaluft.com/ Official website]\n* [https://www.myspace.com/lornaluft Lorna Luft] at MySpace\n* {{IMDb name|5167}}\n* {{IBDB name}}\n* {{iobdb name|16249}}\n* [http://www.broadwayworld.com/viewcolumn.cfm?colid=29791 July 2008 interview with Lorna Luft] on BroadwayWorld.com\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Luft, Lorna}}\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Santa Monica, California]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American stage actresses]]\n[[Category:American musical theatre actresses]]\n[[Category:People with cancer]]\n[[Category:20th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:20th-century American singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:20th-century American women singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women singers]]\n", "name_user": "Moe1810", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eStage productions", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lorna_Luft"}
{"title_page": "International Ecological Economy Promotion Association", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox  \n | title   = International Ecological Economy Promotion Association\n | image = \n | caption = Official logo\n |  label2 = Abbreviation       |   data2 = IEEPA \n |  label3 = Established      |   data3 = 21 October 2015\n |  label4 = Type      |   data4 = International Non-profit\n                                   Environmental Protection\n |  label5 = Headquarters |   data5 = Beijing, China\n |  label6 = Staff |   data6 = 11-50\n |  label7 = Website |   data7 = http://ieepa.org/\n}}\nThe '''International Ecological Economy Promotion Association (IEEPA)''' is a professional [[non-governmental organization]] based in [[Beijing]], [[China]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.gov.cn/news/top_news/2015/02/02/content_281475049158606.htm |title=\u2018New normal\u2019 brings new opportunity for low-carbon economy |website=english.gov.cn |publisher=[[State Council of the People's Republic of China]] |access-date=2018-10-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170716132749/http://english.gov.cn/news/top_news/2015/02/02/content_281475049158606.htm |archive-date=2017-07-16 |url-status=live }}</ref> The IEEPA works on promoting international [[energy conservation]], [[environmental protection]] and [[sustainable development]] and in particular the [[Ecological economics|ecological economy]].\n\n== History ==\nThe IEEPA was founded in 2007 and was officially registered on 21 October 2015, before this the IEEPA was known as the International Energy Conservation and Environmental Protection Association.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bjsstb.gov.cn/wssb/wssb/dc/orgInfo.do?action=seeParticular&orgId=000010000012482&websitId=100&netTypeId=2|title=Social Organisation Management Office-Beijing|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181008060037/http://www.bjsstb.gov.cn/wssb/wssb/dc/orgInfo.do?action=seeParticular&orgId=000010000012482&websitId=100&netTypeId=2|archive-date=2018-10-08|url-status=live}}</ref> The IEEPA, since 2015, has made attempts to promote the ecological economy.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://china.huanqiu.com/hot/2016-07/9114849.html|title=Huanqiu|last=|first=|date=2016-07-02|work=|access-date=2018-07-29}}</ref> During this transition the IEEPA continued to carry out many of the functions and responsibilities previously held by the Energy Conservation and Environmental Protection Association.\n\n== Governance ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Board of Directors\n!Background\n|- \n| [[File:Dr. Hao Jiming.jpg|thumb|Dr. Hao Jiming, President of the IEEPA and Academician at the Chinese Academy of Engineering.]]\n|The current president of the IEEPA, [[Hao Jiming]], has been recognized for his influential work on emission control strategies to challenging the severe [[air pollution in China]] over the last forty years. His notable achievements include successfully designing mitigation plans in acid deposition and urban vehicle pollution control.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.arb.ca.gov/research/hsawards/winners/2015winners.htm|title=Clean Air Leadership Talks with the 2015 Haagen-Smit Clean Air Award Winners|website=California Air Resource Board|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171220011440/https://www.arb.ca.gov/research/hsawards/winners/2015winners.htm|archive-date=2017-12-20|access-date=2018-07-30}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:LiJunyang.jpg|thumb|Li Junyang, Executive Vice-President of the IEEPA; Senior Research Fellow at Tsinghua University's Institute of Environmental Science and Engineering; Senior Research Fellow at Nankai University's Institute of Environmental Science and Engineering.]]\n| Li Junyang has served as the Executive Vice-President of the IEEPA since 2015. Li Junyang has led previous efforts by the IEEPA to improve ecological, social and grassroots governance in China as well as ecological poverty alleviation efforts in Hubei province.\n|}\n\n== Objectives ==\nIEEPA has identified three key operating areas:<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://2013.wec-wec.net/N_Info.aspx?t=2619|title=WEC|website=World Economic and Environmental Conference|access-date=2018-07-29}}</ref>\n\n#''Research and Construction of Domestic and Foreign Policy Issues.'' The IEEPA has ambitions of\u00a0 assembling experts from a wide range of sectors including research, expert resources, academics policy institutes and international agencies to cooperate together.\n#''System Solutions Program for Urban Development.'' Within the regional and urban areas, IEEPA aims to work towards creating green development measures, through the innovative market model of accelerating energy saving technology.\n#''Energy Conservation and Environmental Protection Promotional System.'' A priority of the IEEPA is to promote enterprise projects that have demonstrated potential growth, while focusing on the utilization of resources through sustainable management and energy efficiency.\n\n== Activities ==\nThe IEEPA, since its creation,  has collaborated with a number of organisations domestically and internationally. In 2013 the IEEPA co-launched The Global Innovation Centre for Nano-Fibre Application (GICNA) with the Czech Nafigate Corp to advance technological innovation in green environment.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/business/2013-04/27/content_16457730.htm|title=China Daily|work=China Daily|access-date=2018-07-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131205074018/http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/business/2013-04/27/content_16457730.htm|archive-date=2013-12-05|url-status=live}}</ref> Such innovation included clean water resources, clean air and energy conservation.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/business/2013-04/27/content_16457730.htm|title=China Daily|work=China Daily|access-date=2018-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131205074018/http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/business/2013-04/27/content_16457730.htm|archive-date=2013-12-05|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, the IEEPA worked together with non-governmental organisations from South Korea. Such cooperation included Sung Information Co. Ltd, a South Korean solution service provider who donated equipment to the Chinese Primary Health Care Foundation (CPHCF).<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bjreview.com/se/txt/2015-03/26/content_683334.htm|title=Beijing Review|work=Beijing Review|access-date=2018-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181008060037/http://www.bjreview.com/se/txt/2015-03/26/content_683334.htm|archive-date=2018-10-08|url-status=live}}</ref> The IEEPA saw this collaboration as a way of advancing public health programs in poverty stricken regions within China. The IEEPA sees the cooperation between different charities beyond China as building a platform for research and development between China and other States.{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n\nAs part of the organising committee for the World Economic and Environmental Conference (WEC), the IEEPA has been a constant participant in the annual conference. The WEC was initially formed by the United Nations Green New Deal in 2008 with over 6000 participants from nearly 60 countries and many international organisations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wec-wec.net/Award_info.aspx?type=0|title=The World Economic and Environmental Conference\uff08WEC\uff09|website=WEC|access-date=2017-07-29}}</ref> The conference was set up to promote sustainable development of the world economy but also to advance the ecological economy.{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n\n== References ==\n<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wec-wec.net/N_Info.aspx?t=2619 |title=International Ecological Economy Promotion Association |website=wec-wec.net |publisher=World Economic and Environmental Conference }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.climateaction.org/news/china_south_korea_agreement_to_boost_clean_energy_collaboration |title=China, South Korea agreement to boost clean energy collaboration |website=climateaction.org |publisher=Climate Action |author=William Brittlebank |date=28 July 2014 |access-date=2018-10-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181008060036/http://www.climateaction.org/news/china_south_korea_agreement_to_boost_clean_energy_collaboration |archive-date=2018-10-08 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.businesswirechina.com/en/news/15432.html |title=The 5th WEC Announced its Opening Ceremony was to be Held in November in Beijing |website=businesswirechina.com |publisher=Businesswire China |access-date=2018-10-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181008060036/http://www.businesswirechina.com/en/news/15432.html |archive-date=2018-10-08 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://cleanairasia.org/node7246/ |title=4th World Economic and Environmental Conference (WEC) |website=cleanairasia.org |publisher=Clean Air Asia }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://cn.swisscham.org/event/2014-07-26/first-international-energy-conservation-environmental-protection |title=... |website=cn.swisscham.org |publisher=Swiss Cham |access-date=2018-10-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140721132742/http://cn.swisscham.org/event/2014-07-26/first-international-energy-conservation-environmental-protection |archive-date=2014-07-21 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eco-business.com/news/china-s-korea-seek-to-cut-emissions-in-daily-life/ |title=China, S. Korea seek to cut emissions in daily life |website=eco-business.com |publisher=Eco-Business |access-date=2018-10-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180113121023/http://www.eco-business.com/news/china-s-korea-seek-to-cut-emissions-in-daily-life/ |archive-date=2018-01-13 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://china.org.cn/china/2016-07/25/content_38951788.htm |title=Research to address health impact of indoor air pollution |website=china.org.cn |publisher=China.org.cn |author=Wang Wei |date=25 July 2016 |access-date=2018-10-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160811230819/http://www.china.org.cn/china/2016-07/25/content_38951788.htm |archive-date=2016-08-11 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n<!-- Per [[WP:ELMINOFFICIAL]], choose one official website only -->\n*{{Official website|http://www.ieepa.org.cn/}}\n\n[[Category:Conservation and environmental foundations]]\n[[Category:Environmental organizations based in China]]\n[[Category:Conservation organizations]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in 2015]]\n[[Category:Organizations based in Beijing]]\n[[Category:2015 establishments in China]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox  \n | title   = International Ecological Economy Promotion Association\n | image = \n | caption = Official logo\n |  label2 = Abbreviation       |   data2 = IEEPA \n |  label3 = Established      |   data3 = 21 October 2015\n |  label4 = Type      |   data4 = International Non-profit\n                                   Environmental Protection\n |  label5 = Headquarters |   data5 = Beijing, China\n |  label6 = Staff |   data6 = 11-50\n |  label7 = Website |   data7 = http://ieepa.org/\n}}\nThe '''International Ecological Economy Promotion Association (IEEPA)''' is a professional [[non-governmental organization]] based in [[Beijing]], [[China]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.gov.cn/news/top_news/2015/02/02/content_281475049158606.htm |title=\u2018New normal\u2019 brings new opportunity for low-carbon economy |website=english.gov.cn |publisher=[[State Council of the People's Republic of China]] |access-date=2018-10-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170716132749/http://english.gov.cn/news/top_news/2015/02/02/content_281475049158606.htm |archive-date=2017-07-16 |url-status=live }}</ref> The IEEPA works on promoting international [[energy conservation]], [[environmental protection]] and [[sustainable development]] and in particular the [[Ecological economics|ecological economy]].\n\n== History ==\nThe IEEPA was founded in 2007 and was officially registered on 21 October 2015, before this the IEEPA was known as the International Energy Conservation and Environmental Protection Association.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bjsstb.gov.cn/wssb/wssb/dc/orgInfo.do?action=seeParticular&orgId=000010000012482&websitId=100&netTypeId=2|title=Social Organisation Management Office-Beijing|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181008060037/http://www.bjsstb.gov.cn/wssb/wssb/dc/orgInfo.do?action=seeParticular&orgId=000010000012482&websitId=100&netTypeId=2|archive-date=2018-10-08|url-status=live}}</ref> The IEEPA, since 2015, has made attempts to promote the ecological economy.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://china.huanqiu.com/hot/2016-07/9114849.html|title=Huanqiu|last=|first=|date=2016-07-02|work=|access-date=2018-07-29}}</ref> During this transition the IEEPA continued to carry out many of the functions and responsibilities previously held by the Energy Conservation and Environmental Protection Association.\n\n== Governance ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Board of Directors\n!Background\n|- \n| [[File:Dr. Hao Jiming.jpg|thumb|Dr. Hao Jiming, President of the IEEPA and Academician at the Chinese Academy of Engineering.]]\n|The current president of the IEEPA, [[Hao Jiming]], has been recognized for his influential work on emission control strategies to challenging the severe [[air pollution in China]] over the last forty years. His notable achievements include successfully designing mitigation plans in acid deposition and urban vehicle pollution control.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.arb.ca.gov/research/hsawards/winners/2015winners.htm|title=Clean Air Leadership Talks with the 2015 Haagen-Smit Clean Air Award Winners|website=California Air Resource Board|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171220011440/https://www.arb.ca.gov/research/hsawards/winners/2015winners.htm|archive-date=2017-12-20|access-date=2018-07-30}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:LiJunyang.jpg|thumb|Li Junyang, Executive Vice-President of the IEEPA; Senior Research Fellow at Tsinghua University's Institute of Environmental Science and Engineering; Senior Research Fellow at Nankai University's Institute of Environmental Science and Engineering.]]\n| Li Junyang has served as the Executive Vice-President of the IEEPA since 2015. Li Junyang has led previous efforts by the IEEPA to improve ecological, social and grassroots governance in China as well as ecological poverty alleviation efforts in Hubei province.\n|}\n\n== Objectives ==\nIEEPA has identified three key operating areas:<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://2013.wec-wec.net/N_Info.aspx?t=2619|title=WEC|website=World Economic and Environmental Conference|access-date=2018-07-29}}</ref>\n\n#''Research and Construction of Domestic and Foreign Policy Issues.'' The IEEPA has ambitions of\u00a0 assembling experts from a wide range of sectors including research, expert resources, academics policy institutes and international agencies to cooperate together.\n#''System Solutions Program for Urban Development.'' Within the regional and urban areas, IEEPA aims to work towards creating green development measures, through the innovative market model of accelerating energy saving technology.\n#''Energy Conservation and Environmental Protection Promotional System.'' A priority of the IEEPA is to promote enterprise projects that have demonstrated potential growth, while focusing on the utilization of resources through sustainable management and energy efficiency.\n\n== Activities ==\nThe IEEPA, since its creation,  has collaborated with a number of organisations domestically and internationally. In 2013 the IEEPA co-launched The Global Innovation Centre for Nano-Fibre Application (GICNA) with the Czech Nafigate Corp to advance technological innovation in green environment.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/business/2013-04/27/content_16457730.htm|title=China Daily|work=China Daily|access-date=2018-07-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131205074018/http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/business/2013-04/27/content_16457730.htm|archive-date=2013-12-05|url-status=live}}</ref> Such innovation included clean water resources, clean air and energy conservation.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/business/2013-04/27/content_16457730.htm|title=China Daily|work=China Daily|access-date=2018-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131205074018/http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/business/2013-04/27/content_16457730.htm|archive-date=2013-12-05|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, the IEEPA worked together with non-governmental organisations from South Korea. Such cooperation included Sung Information Co. Ltd, a South Korean solution service provider who donated equipment to the Chinese Primary Health Care Foundation (CPHCF).<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bjreview.com/se/txt/2015-03/26/content_683334.htm|title=Beijing Review|work=Beijing Review|access-date=2018-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181008060037/http://www.bjreview.com/se/txt/2015-03/26/content_683334.htm|archive-date=2018-10-08|url-status=live}}</ref> The IEEPA saw this collaboration as a way of advancing public health programs in poverty stricken regions within China. The IEEPA sees the cooperation between different charities beyond China as building a platform for research and development between China and other States.{{fact|date=February 2020}}\n\nAs part of the organising committee for the World Economic and Environmental Conference (WEC), the IEEPA has been a constant participant in the annual conference. The WEC was initially formed by the United Nations Green New Deal in 2008 with over 6000 participants from nearly 60 countries and many international organisations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wec-wec.net/Award_info.aspx?type=0|title=The World Economic and Environmental Conference\uff08WEC\uff09|website=WEC|access-date=2017-07-29}}</ref> The conference was set up to promote sustainable development of the world economy but also to advance the ecological economy.{{fact|date=February 2020}}\n\n== References ==\n<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wec-wec.net/N_Info.aspx?t=2619 |title=International Ecological Economy Promotion Association |website=wec-wec.net |publisher=World Economic and Environmental Conference }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.climateaction.org/news/china_south_korea_agreement_to_boost_clean_energy_collaboration |title=China, South Korea agreement to boost clean energy collaboration |website=climateaction.org |publisher=Climate Action |author=William Brittlebank |date=28 July 2014 |access-date=2018-10-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181008060036/http://www.climateaction.org/news/china_south_korea_agreement_to_boost_clean_energy_collaboration |archive-date=2018-10-08 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.businesswirechina.com/en/news/15432.html |title=The 5th WEC Announced its Opening Ceremony was to be Held in November in Beijing |website=businesswirechina.com |publisher=Businesswire China |access-date=2018-10-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181008060036/http://www.businesswirechina.com/en/news/15432.html |archive-date=2018-10-08 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://cleanairasia.org/node7246/ |title=4th World Economic and Environmental Conference (WEC) |website=cleanairasia.org |publisher=Clean Air Asia }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://cn.swisscham.org/event/2014-07-26/first-international-energy-conservation-environmental-protection |title=... |website=cn.swisscham.org |publisher=Swiss Cham |access-date=2018-10-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140721132742/http://cn.swisscham.org/event/2014-07-26/first-international-energy-conservation-environmental-protection |archive-date=2014-07-21 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eco-business.com/news/china-s-korea-seek-to-cut-emissions-in-daily-life/ |title=China, S. Korea seek to cut emissions in daily life |website=eco-business.com |publisher=Eco-Business |access-date=2018-10-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180113121023/http://www.eco-business.com/news/china-s-korea-seek-to-cut-emissions-in-daily-life/ |archive-date=2018-01-13 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://china.org.cn/china/2016-07/25/content_38951788.htm |title=Research to address health impact of indoor air pollution |website=china.org.cn |publisher=China.org.cn |author=Wang Wei |date=25 July 2016 |access-date=2018-10-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160811230819/http://www.china.org.cn/china/2016-07/25/content_38951788.htm |archive-date=2016-08-11 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n<!-- Per [[WP:ELMINOFFICIAL]], choose one official website only -->\n*{{Official website|http://www.ieepa.org.cn/}}\n\n[[Category:Conservation and environmental foundations]]\n[[Category:Environmental organizations based in China]]\n[[Category:Conservation organizations]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in 2015]]\n[[Category:Organizations based in Beijing]]\n[[Category:2015 establishments in China]]\n", "name_user": "CAPTAIN RAJU", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Ecological_Economy_Promotion_Association"}
